comment.shortText:
create() provides a simple factory for generating activityPub objects. This
method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: An activity pub object

comment.shortText:
hash() provides a simple way to hash activityPub objects while guaranteeing
that identical objects with different key orders still return the same hash.
The underlying hash method used is [Keccak256](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA-3).
comment.returns: A hexadecimal string containing the Keccak hash

comment.text: The activity pub object to hash

comment.shortText:
validate() returns true if the object provided is a valid activityPub.
Otherwise, it returns false. This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: True or false depending on whether the given object is a valid

comment.shortText:
createFile() takes a series of activity pub objects and returns a Batch file
object for publishing. This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: A batch file object

tags.text: events  An array of DSNPEvents to include in the batch file

comment.shortText: openFile() takes a Batch file object . This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: An array of DSNPEvents from the batch file

tags.text: file  A batch file object to open

comment.shortText:
dequeue() implements the dequeue function of the QueueInterface. It takes an
id, removes any events in the queue with matching ids and returns the removed
event. This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: The removed event

comment.shortText:
enqueue() implements the enqueue function of the QueueInterface. It takes a
DSNP event, adds it to an in-memory store and returns an id which can be used
to reverse this action, if needed. This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: A queue id to be used to remove the event if needed

comment.shortText:
getAll() implements the getAll function of the QueueInterface. It returns an
array of all items currently in the queue and clears the queue. This method
is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: An array of all events currently in the queue

comment.shortText:
commit() creates a batch file from the current activity pub events in the
queue then clears the queue. This method is not yet implemented.

dequeue() removes an activity pub event from the queue for later publishing
to the blockchain. This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: The DSNP event event removed from the queue

comment.shortText:
enqueue() adds an activity pub event to the queue for later publishing to the
blockchain as a batch file. This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: An ID for the queued event

comment.shortText:
getConfig() fetches the current configuration settings and returns them. This
method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: The current configuration settings

comment.shortText:
setConfig() sets the current configuration with the given object. This method
is not yet implemented.

tags.text: obj  The configuration settings to set with

comment.shortText:
batch() allows users call the batch smart contract and post the URI and hash
of a generated batch to the blockchain.
comment.returns: A [web3 contract receipt promise](https://web3js.readthedocs.io/en/v1.3.4/web3-eth-contract.html#id36)

comment.text: The web3 instance used for calling the smart contract
The address from which to post the batch
The URI of the hosted batch to post
A hash of the batch contents for use in verification

comment.shortText:
broadcast() creates a broadcast DSNP event and enqueues it for the next
batch. This method is not yet implemented.

react() creates a reaction activity pub event and enqueues it for the next
batch. This method is not yet implemented.

reply() creates a reply activity pub event and enqueues it for the next
batch. This method is not yet implemented.

addressToHandles() takes a DSNP identity address and returns an array of all
associated DSNP handles. This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: An array of DSNP handles associated with the address

comment.shortText:
authenticateHandle() claims a registry handle to the current user. If the
given handle has not yet been claimed, the handle will be claimed by the
current configured DSNP address. If the handle has been previously claimed by
the current address, the handle will be set to the active handle and used for
all events created on chain. If the handle has been previously claimed by an
address other than the current DSNP address, an error will be thrown. This
method is very much not yet implemented.

getUser() fetches information regarding the current published state of a
given user by handle. This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: The User object associated with the given Handle

comment.shortText:
handleToAddress() takes a DSNP handle and returns the associated DSNP
identity address. This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: The DSNP address associated with the given handle

comment.shortText:
updateUser() updates profile data for the user given by handle. This method
will only work if the given handle has already been authenticated. This
method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: The User object associated with the given Handle

comment.shortText:
follow() creates a follow event and enqueues it for the next batch. This
method is not yet implemented.

getFollowees() scans the current state of the network and returns an array of
all user handles being followed by the given follower handle. This method is
not yet implemented.
comment.returns: An array of all users followed by the follower user

comment.shortText:
getFollowers() scans the current state of the network and returns an array of
all user handles following the given followee handle. This method is not yet
implemented.
comment.returns: An array of all users following the followee

comment.shortText:
isFollowing() scans the current state of the network and returns a boolean
representing whether or not a given user is following another given user.
This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: A boolean representing whether or not the follower is following the followee

comment.shortText:
unfollow() creates an unfollow event and enqueues it for the next batch.
This method is not yet implemented.

tags.text: {string[]} types          The type of events to fetch, i.e. "notes", "follows" etc.
{Handle[]} includeHandles List of user handles to fetch events from. If not present, all users not listed in excludeHandles will be included.
{Handle[]} excludeHandles List of user handles to exclude from results, such as a blocklist.
{HexString[]} inReplyTo  List of hashes to seek replies to. For use in fetching comments and reactions.

comment.shortText:
fetchEvents() fetches the most recent activity pub events matching the given
search criteria. This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: An array of events

comment.shortText:
subscribe() takes a callback to invoke upon receiving new activity pub events
matching the given criteria. This method only works if the web3 provider set
in the configuration is a websocket provider. This method is not yet
implemented.
comment.returns: A subscription id to unsubscribe later if needed

comment.shortText:
unsubscribe() removes a subscription callback created with the subscribe
method. This method only works if the web3 provider set in the configuration
is a websocket provider. This method is not yet implemented.

fetch() implements the fetch function of the StorageInterface. It takes the
URI of a file to fetch and returns the file. This method is not yet
implemented.
comment.returns: The fetched file

comment.shortText:
store() implements the store function of the StorageInterface. It takes a
file object to store and returns a URI for the stored data. This method is
not yet implemented.
comment.returns: The URI of the stored file

comment.shortText:
fetch() takes a URI and fetches a batch file from the given address. This
method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: The batch file fetched from the given URI

tags.text:
HTTPError
Indicates an error was thrown at the HTTP layer. This may indicate that the
host has censored the content for legal reasons if the error code is 451.

comment.shortText:
store() takes a batch file to store with the chosen hosting solution and
returns the URI of the file once stored. This method is not yet implemented.
comment.returns: The URI of the hosted file

sortObject() takes a javascript object and returns a copy of the object with
all keys sorted recursively. This method is intended to be used to guarantee
that objects intended be JSON stringified always produce a consistent JSON
string, since implementations of [JSON.stringify](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/JSON/stringify#issue_with_plain_json.stringify_for_use_as_javascript)
do not necessarily guarantee key order.
comment.returns: A sorted copy of the given object
